tool_description: Diceware generated passwords that you can easily remember
title: Mad-Libs-Diceware

api_list.name: /madlibs-wordlist
api_list.description: **Get the wordlist used by madlibs diceware in JSON format**
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://mad-libs-diceware.p.rapidapi.com/madlibs-wordlist"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "mad-libs-diceware.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

api_list.name: /madlibs-diceware
api_list.description:
**Generate password using madlibs diceware**

Use query string parameter *nphrase* to change number of phrases in the password

The generated phrase/s have the following structure: 

```<adverb> <adjective> <noun>```

Accepted values for *nphrases* parameter: 1 and 2
